(42, 18, 22, 42, 9, 57, 62, 'follow me', 'Call to Discipleship', 'Both passages emphasize the cost of following Jesus. In Luke 18:22, Jesus instructs selling possessions, while in Luke 9:57-62, He highlights the sacrifices required for discipleship.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 22, 19, 27, 4, 4, 'one thing', 'Desire for Spiritual Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking a singular focus on spiritual fulfillment. Both passages emphasize the importance of prioritizing one''s relationship with God over material possessions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 22, 44, 2, 44, 45, 'sell all that thou hast', 'Connection of Generosity and Community', 'Both passages emphasize the act of selling possessions and distributing to those in need. This connection highlights a shared theme of communal support and prioritizing spiritual wealth over material goods.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 23, 26, 33, 31, 31, 'very rich', 'Connection of Wealth and Covetousness', 'This connection highlights the sorrow of the rich man in Luke, who is tied to his wealth, paralleling the people in Ezekiel who show love but pursue covetousness. Both passages emphasize the conflict between outward appearances and inner desires.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 23, 62, 2, 15, 15, 'very rich', 'Connection of Wealth and Worldly Love', 'This connection highlights the sorrow of prioritizing wealth over spiritual values. Both passages emphasize the conflict between attachment to riches and the love of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 23, 18, 31, 24, 25, 'very sorrowful', 'Wealth and Sorrow Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the sorrow associated with wealth. In Luke, the rich man is sorrowful due to his possessions, while Job reflects on the dangers of placing hope in gold and wealth.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 23, 40, 19, 22, 22, 'sorrowful', 'Connection of Sorrow and Wealth', 'Both passages emphasize the sorrow of the young man due to his wealth. The phrases ''very sorrowful'' and ''went away sorrowful'' highlight his emotional response to the call to give up his possessions.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 23, 41, 10, 22, 22, 'very sorrowful', 'Emotional Response to Wealth', 'Both passages emphasize the sorrowful reaction of a wealthy individual when faced with the call to give up his possessions. The phrases ''very sorrowful'' and ''sad at that saying'' highlight a shared emotional response to the challenge of wealth.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 23, 42, 8, 14, 14, 'very rich', 'Connection of Riches and Spiritual Fruit', 'Both passages emphasize the challenges posed by wealth. In Luke 18:23, the rich man''s sorrow reflects the struggle with attachment to riches, while Luke 8:14 highlights how cares and riches can choke spiritual growth.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 23, 42, 12, 15, 15, 'very rich', 'Connection of Wealth and Life''s Value', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between wealth and spiritual well-being. The sorrow of the rich man in Luke 18:23 reflects the warning against covetousness in Luke 12:15, highlighting that true life is not defined by material abundance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 24, 20, 11, 28, 28, 'they that have riches', 'Connection Between Wealth and Trust', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of trusting in riches. Luke 18:24 warns that those with riches face difficulty entering the kingdom of God, while Proverbs 11:28 states that trusting in riches leads to downfall.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 24, 20, 30, 9, 9, 'riches enter into the kingdom of God', 'Wealth and Spiritual Danger', 'This connection highlights the dangers of wealth in both passages. Luke 18:24 warns that the rich may struggle to enter the kingdom of God, while Proverbs 30:9 expresses concern that wealth can lead to denial of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 24, 41, 10, 23, 27, 'How hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God!', 'Riches and the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the difficulty for those with riches to enter the kingdom of God. They highlight the astonishment of the disciples at this teaching, reinforcing the theme of reliance on wealth versus faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 24, 59, 2, 5, 7, 'riches enter into the kingdom of God', 'Riches and the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the challenges faced by the rich in relation to the kingdom of God. Luke highlights the difficulty for the wealthy to enter, while James points out God''s preference for the poor, who are rich in faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 24, 19, 10, 3, 3, 'riches enter into the kingdom of God', 'Wealth and Spiritual Struggle', 'Both passages emphasize the negative view of wealth and its impact on spiritual well-being. Luke highlights the difficulty for the rich to enter God''s kingdom, while Psalms condemns the covetous, whom God abhors.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 24, 40, 19, 23, 25, 'How hardly shall they that have riches', 'Riches and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the difficulty for the wealthy to enter the kingdom of God. The imagery of a camel going through the eye of a needle in Matthew reinforces the message found in Luke about the sorrow of the rich. This connection highlights a shared theme of the challenges faced by those with riches.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 24, 5, 6, 10, 12, 'How hardly shall they that have riches', 'Wealth and Spiritual Warning', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of forgetting God in the face of material abundance. In Luke, Jesus warns about the difficulty for the wealthy to enter the kingdom of God, while Deuteronomy cautions against forgetting the Lord after receiving blessings.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 25, 40, 23, 24, 24, 'camel', 'Camel Imagery in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of a camel, highlighting the difficulty of entering the kingdom of God. This connection illustrates the contrast between the insignificant and the significant in spiritual matters.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 26, 42, 13, 23, 23, 'Who then can be saved?', 'Questions about Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize inquiries regarding salvation, reflecting a concern about who can be saved. The question in Luke 18:26 directly relates to the inquiry in Luke 13:23 about the number of those who will be saved.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 27, 24, 32, 17, 17, NULL, 'God''s Power Over Human Limitations', 'Both passages emphasize that there is nothing too hard for God. Luke highlights the impossibility of human efforts, while Jeremiah affirms God''s great power in creation, reinforcing the theme of divine capability.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 27, 40, 19, 26, 26, NULL, 'Possibility with God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of impossibility with men contrasted with the possibility of God. They convey a similar message about divine capability in situations beyond human ability.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 27, 42, 1, 37, 37, NULL, 'God''s Power Over Human Limitations', 'Both passages emphasize that with God, nothing is impossible. This connection highlights the theme of divine capability in contrast to human limitations.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 27, 18, 42, 2, 2, 'the things which are impossible with men', 'Divine Possibility and Power', 'Both passages emphasize God''s omnipotence and ability to accomplish what is beyond human capability. Luke highlights that what is impossible for men is possible for God, while Job acknowledges that God can do everything.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 27, 1, 18, 14, 14, 'the things which are impossible with men', 'Divine Possibility and Human Limitation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of God''s ability to accomplish what seems impossible to humans. In Genesis, the question ''Is any thing too hard for the Lord?'' directly parallels the assertion in Luke that ''the things which are impossible with men are possible with God.''', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 27, 49, 1, 19, 20, 'impossible with men are possible with God', 'Divine Power and Possibility', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s power to accomplish what is impossible for humans. Both passages emphasize the greatness of God''s power, particularly in the context of miraculous events, such as the resurrection of Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 27, 27, 4, 35, 35, 'impossible with men', 'Divine Sovereignty and Possibility', 'Both passages emphasize God''s power to accomplish what seems impossible to humans. Luke highlights that what is impossible with men is possible with God, while Daniel asserts that God acts according to His will, unchallenged by anyone.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 28, 41, 10, 28, 28, 'Lo, we have left all, and followed thee.', 'Peter''s Declaration of Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize Peter''s acknowledgment of leaving everything to follow Jesus. The similar phrasing in both verses highlights the theme of discipleship and commitment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 28, 50, 3, 7, 7, 'left all, and followed thee', 'Loss for Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of sacrifice for the sake of following Christ. Both passages emphasize leaving behind personal gains or possessions in pursuit of a deeper relationship with Him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 28, 40, 19, 27, 27, 'we have left all, and followed thee', 'Peter''s Declaration of Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize Peter''s acknowledgment of leaving everything to follow Jesus. The phrases ''left all'' and ''forsaken all'' highlight the same commitment to discipleship.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 28, 42, 5, 11, 11, NULL, 'Disciples'' Commitment to Follow', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' decision to forsake everything in order to follow Jesus. This shared theme of leaving behind their former lives illustrates the total commitment required to be His followers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
